author: Jake Boyer
title: Watch Alex Trebek Rap Kanye, Lil Wayne & Drake on ‘Jeopardy!’
text:
Last year, during a particularly wonderful episode of everyone’s favorite primetime game show Jeopardy!, host Alex Trebek flawlessly rapped a few bars from Drake’s “Jumpan”. Why this 2015 track was a clue in the first place is irrelevant, as it showed that Trebek has some intriguingly preternatural skills at throwing down on a beat. But this feat was but the tip of the iceberg, as on last night’s program he rapped Drake again, in addition to Kanye and Kendrick. Watch him go below.
How about Alex Trebek rapping on Jeopardy! tonight pic.twitter.com/MNy9CEkf1p 
— Kenny Ducey (@KennyDucey) February 21, 2017 

The category was called ‘Let’s Rap, Kids!’, and across the five clues were hidden lyrics from the excellent roster of Drake, Kendrick Lamar, Lil Wayne and Kanye West. But the final clue really takes the cake, as it features Trebek rapping the immortal lines from Desiigner’s “Panda”: “Panda, panda, panda, panda, panda.”
